Let be a commutative ring, let be an -module, and let be an element of . One says that is -regular if the multiplication by map formula_42 is injective, and that is a zero divisor on otherwise. The set of -regular elements is a multiplicative set in .
Specializing the definitions of "-regular" and "zero divisor on " to the case = recovers the definitions of "regular" and "zero divisor" given earlier in this article.

